# SWITCH

Este comando permite **ejecutar un bloque de código distinto** en función del valor de una variable.

.pull-left[

```r
#La sentencia tiene la siguiente estructura:
1 switch ( &lt;Expr&gt; ,
2 &lt;valor_1&gt;{
3 # código
4 },
5 …
6 &lt;valor_n&gt;{
7 #codigo
8 }
9 ) #Termina switch
```
]

.pull-right[

```r
#Ejemplo sencillo:
 x &lt;- 1:10
 type &lt;- "mean"
 switch(type,
 mean = mean(x),
 median = median(x),
 sd = sd(x)
 )
```

```
## [1] 5.5
```
]

---


```r
x &lt;- as.integer(2)
z &lt;- switch(x,1,2,3,4,5)
z
```

```
## [1] 2
```

```r
x &lt;- 3.5
z &lt;- switch(x,1,2,3,4,5)
z
```

```
## [1] 3
```

```r
y &lt;- rnorm(5)
x &lt;- "sd"
z &lt;- switch(x,"mean"= mean(y),"median"= median(y),"variance"= var(y),"sd"=sd(y))
z
```

```
## [1] 1.048981
```

```r
x &lt;- "median"
z &lt;- switch(x,"mean"= mean(y), "median"= median(y),"variance"= var(y), "sd"=sd(y))
z
```

```
## [1] -0.108966
```

